66536.title: evening dress 'Clouds'
66536.provenance:
Private Collection, Los Angeles; {1} (Leslie Hindman Auctioneers, Chicago, Illinois); purchased by the Indianapolis Museum of Art in 2009.

{1} See catalogue, Leslie Hindman Auctioneers, Vintage Couture and Accessories, 21 September 2008, lot 132.
66536.inscription:
label: Halston
label: Martha / Palm Beach, New York, Miami Beach

extended_text.content: After a visit to Japan in 1980, Halston sought out the Japanese textile designer Reiko Sudo (b. 1953) for collaboration. Sudo’s hand-painted designs soon replaced the perennially popular tie-dyed prints that were characteristic of Halston’s collections. Taking its inspiration from organic forms and nature, the original cloud print for this dress was hand-painted on silk by Sudo and later reprinted. Iridescent clear sequins cover the entire surface of the dress, giving it a subtle luster and sheen.
extended_text.title: Gallery Label
